    <name>fooyin</name>
    <summary>A customisable music player</summary>
    <developer id="org.fooyin.luketaylor">
        <name>Luke Taylor</name>
    </developer>
    <description>
        <p>
            fooyin is a music player built around customisation.
            It provides a variety of widgets to help you manage and play your local collection.
            It's highly extensible with a plugin system and includes FooScript,
            a scripting language for advanced configuration of widgets.
        </p>
        <p>Features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Fully customisable layout, starting from a blank window</li>
            <li>Playback of most popular formats, including VGM</li>
            <li>Gapless playback</li>
            <li>Add and play files from within archives</li>
            <li>Audio output and device configuration</li>
            <li>CUE sheet support (including embedded)</li>
            <li>Customisable keyboard shortcuts</li>
            <li>Filter library on any field(s)</li>
            <li>Create and manage playlists</li>
            <li>Import/export playlists (M3U/M3U8)</li>
            <li>Extensible using a plugin system</li>
            <li>Tag editing</li>
            <li>Library tree, including directory structure view</li>
            <li>Directory browser</li>
            <li>Waveform seekbar</li>
            <li>MPRIS support</li>
            <li>Scrobbling</li>
        </ul>
    </description>
